1
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:49,200
Tell me how Zero cured your poison.

2
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:51,359
My Lord.

3
00:01:51,959 --> 00:01:53,120
I don't remember anything.

4
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:03,879
The variable Zero completely ruined my plans.

5
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,359
Have you found out his identity?

6
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:10,719
No leads so far.

7
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:18,479
Useless!

8
00:02:24,439 --> 00:02:26,680
The Child Gu inside you

9
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:30,120
has already begun devouring your organs.

10
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:32,520
I'll give you three more days.

11
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:35,439
Retrieve the Soul-Sea Pacifying Art

12
00:02:35,439 --> 00:02:36,879
in exchange for your life.

13
00:03:00,039 --> 00:03:01,879
This Number One really puts on a show.

14
00:03:12,319 --> 00:03:14,080
Number One.

15
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,879
A place that trains Medicine Venerables sure is different.

16
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,479
Hey, buddy.

17
00:03:39,479 --> 00:03:40,719
Let me ask you something.

18
00:03:40,719 --> 00:03:42,280
What's the big occasion today?

19
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:43,759
Why is everyone so dressed up?

20
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:48,000
Today is the Number One Pharmacy's

21
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,479
annual Medicine Apprentice recruitment day.

22
00:03:52,159 --> 00:03:53,400
Do you know how many people

23
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:54,800
have been waiting for this?

24
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,599
That impressive?

25
00:03:57,439 --> 00:03:59,319
Of course.

26
00:03:59,319 --> 00:04:02,639
Not just anyone can get into Number One.

27
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:05,080
It's the very first pharmacy opened

28
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,599
since the Mystic Medicine Association went public.

29
00:04:06,599 --> 00:04:08,879
The greatest Medicine Masters of our age

30
00:04:08,879 --> 00:04:09,960
all came out of this place.

31
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,400
And let me tell you,

32
00:04:14,639 --> 00:04:16,639
the people applying for Medicine Apprentice here

33
00:04:16,639 --> 00:04:17,639
are no ordinary folks.

34
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:20,920
Take a look at this guy.

35
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:24,160
The handsome guy in custom Chinese couture.

36
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:26,920
He's a three-time Medicine King Cup

37
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:28,639
junior division champion.

38
00:04:29,199 --> 00:04:30,040
Wow, amazing.

39
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:34,639
That beauty is the Liang family heiress.

40
00:04:34,639 --> 00:04:36,240
She studied under a famous master.

41
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:39,040
I hear at sixteen she could already brew

42
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:40,639
Mind-Clarifying Pills on her own.

43
00:04:41,519 --> 00:04:42,279
Incredible.

44
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:47,360
Looks like all the top talents have gathered here.

45
00:04:52,519 --> 00:04:54,040
May I ask what your background is, my friend?

46
00:04:55,759 --> 00:04:56,720
Me?

47
00:04:56,720 --> 00:05:00,639
I studied under Master Qinghui of Mount Bailu.

48
00:05:01,639 --> 00:05:04,439
Back in the day, he could debate doctrines

49
00:05:04,439 --> 00:05:06,040
with Floating Light Medicine Venerable

50
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,199
of the Mystic Medicine Association.

51
00:05:08,399 --> 00:05:09,399
Impressive.

52
00:05:09,399 --> 00:05:10,720
I'd love to learn from you.

53
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:12,519
But...

54
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,639
how about you, friend?

55
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:18,120
My master is...

56
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,439
My master is...

57
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:25,360
I just came down from secluded training in the deep mountains.

58
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,879
I guess you could call me

59
00:05:26,879 --> 00:05:28,000
a country backwoods doctor.

60
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,439
A backwoods doctor?

61
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:30,480
What about it?

62
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:32,000
You dare show up at Number One?

63
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,120
You're literally polluting the air here.

64
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,720
Then you'd better be careful.

65
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:38,920
I can see your liver fire is excessive,

66
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:39,839
and your qi flow is in disorder.

67
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:41,480
Don't end up unable to catch your breath

68
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,680
and pass out from it.

69
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:43,399
Why, you...

70
00:05:43,399 --> 00:05:43,920
I...

71
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,600
"I" what? Let me take a look at you.

72
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,759
You're already turning red.

73
00:05:46,759 --> 00:05:48,360
If you really blow a vessel from rage,

74
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,439
this backwoods doctor will have to

75
00:05:49,439 --> 00:05:50,279
treat you, and that's just not worth it.

76
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:51,759
President Ye has arrived!

77
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,399
Who is she?

78
00:06:07,879 --> 00:06:10,000
That's Ye Qingxue, sole heiress of the Ye family from Green Wood Hall.

79
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,879
She runs their entire medical equipment enterprise.

80
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,839
A real business tycoon.

81
00:06:16,199 --> 00:06:17,759
And her legs are pretty long too.

82
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:20,040
She's also the only one who dares to fire people to their faces.

83
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:22,040
Once she fires you, you're done for in this industry.

84
00:06:23,959 --> 00:06:24,639
What a presence.

85
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:33,680
I'll be presiding over today's exam.

86
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:40,720
Anyone who doesn't dare compete still has a chance to leave now.

87
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,600
Show 'em what you got, buddy!

88
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,439
Next time.

89
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:47,399
What a charming couple, huh?

90
00:06:47,399 --> 00:06:48,199
Xiao Qiu.

91
00:06:51,759 --> 00:06:53,000
Tell Mystic Water Hall,

92
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,879
only one Medicine Apprentice is admitted today.

93
00:06:55,639 --> 00:06:56,639
Take him to register.

94
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,480
President Ye, I'm from Mystic Water Hall myself.

95
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,199
Let me take him.

96
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:02,600
Fine.

97
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,519
That saves me the trouble.

98
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:06,800
Let's go.

99
00:07:07,519 --> 00:07:08,800
Just like that, I'm in?

100
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:16,199
President Ye, what you requested has been arranged.

101
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:17,399
Good.

102
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:20,920
Now we'll see if he can pass the assessment.

103
00:07:24,959 --> 00:07:26,199
I've been wondering about something.

104
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:29,639
Why does everyone wear different colored robes?

105
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,079
In the Mystic Medicine Association,

106
00:07:32,079 --> 00:07:34,600
robe colors represent their ranks.

107
00:07:34,839 --> 00:07:36,120
Those in gray

108
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:38,639
are Medicine Apprentices, the newest recruits.

109
00:07:38,639 --> 00:07:40,720
They must pass the annual exam

110
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:44,160
to become blue-robed Pharmacists before they can practice on their own.

111
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:44,879
Don't worry, brother-in-law.

112
00:07:44,879 --> 00:07:45,639
You understand?

113
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:46,759
I'll find that Zero as soon as possible.

114
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:48,480
Understood.

115
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,279
I was just looking for you.

116
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,199
Can't you even hold onto a file?

117
00:07:59,199 --> 00:07:59,879
You okay?

118
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:01,199
I'm fine.

119
00:08:01,199 --> 00:08:02,120
Hurry up and do the ward rounds for me.

120
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,399
Okay, I'll go in a bit.

121
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,319
Go right now.

122
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,319
Don't cause me trouble.

123
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:14,240
You...

124
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:15,639
Brother-in-law.

125
00:08:15,639 --> 00:08:16,600
Who's that raging psycho?

126
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:18,439
Why is he so disrespectful?

127
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,639
He's my younger brother.

128
00:08:20,639 --> 00:08:23,480
Helping him is basically my own family business.

129
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:25,160
Besides, Mingcheng is a Medicine Holder.

130
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,519
He's usually quite busy.

131
00:08:26,519 --> 00:08:28,120
It's only natural for him to assign me tasks.

132
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,480
So what?

133
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,439
Just because his rank is a bit higher,

134
00:08:30,439 --> 00:08:31,399
he gets to bully others as he pleases?

135
00:08:33,759 --> 00:08:34,679
You don't understand.

136
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:38,279
Many can't reach that level in a lifetime.

137
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,240
What's the big deal?

138
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,679
I believe you can do it too.

139
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:46,919
The Holder exam at the Medicine King Festival is held every three years.

140
00:08:46,919 --> 00:08:48,639
Although it's held this year,

141
00:08:48,639 --> 00:08:50,960
only the Green Wood Hall of the Ancient Method faction has openings.

142
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:54,039
The competition is quite fierce.

143
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:57,840
Someone like me has no chance at all.

144
00:08:57,840 --> 00:09:00,879
Plus, between Green Wood Hall and our Lu family,

145
00:09:00,879 --> 00:09:02,039
there's some misunderstanding.

146
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,279
As long as you can heal and save lives,

147
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:06,960
all that other messy stuff doesn't matter.

148
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:12,279
Right.

149
00:09:13,039 --> 00:09:13,919
I'll show you around.

150
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:14,399
Let's go.

151
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,120
This way.

152
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:22,440
What do you think?

153
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,039
This is...

154
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,519
Miss Lu.

155
00:09:28,519 --> 00:09:29,879
You've graced us with your presence.

156
00:09:29,879 --> 00:09:31,559
Is there something you need arranged?

157
00:09:31,559 --> 00:09:33,000
You came in person?

158
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,320
You flatter me too much!

159
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,399
This guy's a real bootlicker.

160
00:09:37,399 --> 00:09:39,519
He's got great skills at sucking up to superiors.

161
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,080
Sir.

162
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,720
No need.

163
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:44,639
At the clinic, I'm just like you,

164
00:09:44,639 --> 00:09:45,519
both Pharmacists.

165
00:09:45,519 --> 00:09:46,440
No need to be so formal.

166
00:09:46,799 --> 00:09:47,480
Right.

167
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,159
Miss Lu...

168
00:09:48,159 --> 00:09:48,840
No,

169
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:49,519
Pharmacist Lu.

170
00:09:52,039 --> 00:09:54,440
This is Wuming, a new Medicine Apprentice.

171
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,519
He just arrived at the clinic.

172
00:09:55,519 --> 00:09:57,240
He's not familiar with some of the rules.

173
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:59,360
Please look after him going forward, Pharmacist.

174
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,240
Hello.

175
00:10:01,279 --> 00:10:02,720
Sir,

176
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:05,240
you can tell at a glance you're quite outstanding.

177
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,399
What an extraordinary aura.

178
00:10:07,399 --> 00:10:09,639
I'll do my very best,

179
00:10:09,639 --> 00:10:10,679
and teach you everything I know.

180
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:12,600
Thanks.

181
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,840
I'll show him around then.

182
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,399
Okay, go ahead.

183
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:20,919
How come you need the bathroom again after just a few minutes?

184
00:10:20,919 --> 00:10:22,039
Tell me about it.

185
00:10:22,039 --> 00:10:24,120
For the past couple of days, I haven't gotten anything done.

186
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,480
I just keep running to the bathroom.

187
00:10:26,159 --> 00:10:27,000
Wait here.

188
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,559
Take your medicine on time when you get back.

189
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:35,759
Pharmacist Ge said

190
00:10:35,759 --> 00:10:36,840
your urination these past few days

191
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:37,799
has been urgent and painful.

192
00:10:37,799 --> 00:10:39,279
It's mainly because of irregular routines,

193
00:10:39,279 --> 00:10:40,399
sitting too long, and not drinking enough water,

194
00:10:40,399 --> 00:10:41,639
causing damp-heat in the lower jiao.

195
00:10:41,639 --> 00:10:44,799
Remember, urinary issues really can't be ignored.

196
00:10:44,799 --> 00:10:45,559
Got it.

197
00:10:45,559 --> 00:10:45,960
Hurry along now.

198
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:46,879
Thank you, Pharmacist.

199
00:10:46,879 --> 00:10:47,440
Don't hold it in!

200
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:48,080
I'll follow your orders faithfully.

201
00:10:49,759 --> 00:10:50,960
This medicine cabinet wall

202
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:53,240
holds the rare herbs of our Mystic Medicine Association.

203
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,200
Take a look.

204
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,399
Impressive.

205
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,960
Purple ganoderma.

206
00:11:07,399 --> 00:11:08,360
From southern Yunnan.

207
00:11:09,759 --> 00:11:10,960
Impressive.

208
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:12,919
I'm a proper Pharmacist, you know.

209
00:11:12,919 --> 00:11:16,080
Identifying origin by an herb's scent

210
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:18,399
isn't a skill exclusive to the Ancient Method faction.

211
00:11:18,399 --> 00:11:20,559
It's a basic skill for any Pharmacist.

212
00:11:21,799 --> 00:11:23,720
No wonder I picked you

213
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,080
as a future Medicine Holder candidate.

214
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:28,919
You're the only one who says that.

215
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:35,000
This medicine cabinet here

216
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,000
holds all of our finished medicines.

217
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,360
Based on their different effects,

218
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,679
they're sorted into several categories.

219
00:11:39,679 --> 00:11:41,159
There's heat-clearing and detoxifying,

220
00:11:41,159 --> 00:11:42,279
blood and qi tonics,

221
00:11:42,279 --> 00:11:43,080
and dampness-draining ones.

222
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,480
This one, for instance, clears heat, detoxifies,

223
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:46,200
unblocks urination, and drains dampness.

224
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:52,399
Pharmacist Lu, please report to the general room immediately.

225
00:11:52,399 --> 00:11:53,440
Go on, attend to your work.

226
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,240
Thanks for today.

227
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,039
You're welcome.

228
00:12:00,519 --> 00:12:01,159
You!

229
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:02,480
Get over here.

230
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,120
I'm talking to you.

231
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:08,120
You're going to mind the counter for me.

232
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:11,200
Fill prescriptions, brew the medicine, and give it to the patients.

233
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,200
And be quick about it.

234
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,000
You hear me?

235
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:16,799
And what about you?

236
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:19,519
Me?

237
00:12:20,919 --> 00:12:23,519
Remember your place.

238
00:12:23,519 --> 00:12:25,120
You're a Medicine Apprentice.

239
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:26,639
I'm a Pharmacist.

240
00:12:26,639 --> 00:12:28,080
What I say goes.

241
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:30,440
Let me tell you,

242
00:12:31,039 --> 00:12:34,000
don't bother me with every little thing.

243
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:36,960
Even if the sky's falling,

244
00:12:39,799 --> 00:12:40,399
go around me.

245
00:12:41,639 --> 00:12:42,639
Don't cause me any trouble.

246
00:12:42,639 --> 00:12:43,279
You hear me?

247
00:12:43,879 --> 00:12:45,720
Yes, I hear you.

248
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,759
Why don't you go catch up on some sleep?

249
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:52,799
Out of my way.

250
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:55,879
You ruined my sweet dream.

251
00:12:56,799 --> 00:12:57,440
I need to make up for it.

252
00:12:59,919 --> 00:13:01,399
You really know how to enjoy yourself.

253
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:05,559
You've totally mastered slacking off at work.

254
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:30,120
The Mystic Medicine Association has quite a lot of good stuff.

255
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,240
The patient's here.

256
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:37,480
This way, please.

257
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:38,519
Slow down, be careful.

258
00:13:41,039 --> 00:13:41,639
Come.

259
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:47,200
This prescription is from the most esteemed Pharmacist.

260
00:13:47,759 --> 00:13:48,879
We must treat it with utmost care.

261
00:13:48,879 --> 00:13:50,519
What prescription is so precious?

262
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,519
Don't you still have to take the medicine?

263
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,320
Come, put your hand here.

264
00:13:56,799 --> 00:13:57,879
Let me check your pulse.

265
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:04,360
Wait...

266
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:05,600
You're just a Medicine...

267
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,240
A Medicine Apprentice knows how to read pulses?

268
00:14:09,399 --> 00:14:12,159
Pharmacists all started as Apprentices, too.

269
00:14:12,159 --> 00:14:13,679
Give young folks more of a chance.

270
00:14:20,039 --> 00:14:21,159
True enough.

271
00:14:32,279 --> 00:14:32,720
You...

272
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,200
Take a look at mine.

273
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:36,559
This...

274
00:14:37,519 --> 00:14:39,600
Alright, I'll write you a new prescription.

275
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,399
Wait, this...

276
00:14:42,399 --> 00:14:43,200
This prescription...

277
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:47,440
Can we trust this?

278
00:14:50,159 --> 00:14:51,039
Here.

279
00:14:51,039 --> 00:14:52,759
Drink it hot, that's when it's most effective.

280
00:14:52,759 --> 00:14:53,200
Drink up.

281
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:54,759
This...

282
00:14:55,879 --> 00:14:56,799
Should I drink this, honey?

283
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,519
Maybe don't drink it. Can we trust this?

284
00:14:59,519 --> 00:15:00,799
Don't be afraid.

285
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:02,799
This illness of yours...

286
00:15:02,799 --> 00:15:04,240
is indeed a bit tricky.

287
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,759
But luckily, you've come across me.

288
00:15:07,559 --> 00:15:09,720
If you really took the medicine on that prescription,

289
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,679
who knows how long it'd drag on.

290
00:15:33,639 --> 00:15:34,559
Honey.

291
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:36,120
Honey, are you alright?

292
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:37,279
Somebody, come!

293
00:15:37,279 --> 00:15:38,720
Something's happened!

294
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:39,720
Somebody!

295
00:15:46,639 --> 00:15:47,759
Keep your eyes on him.
